<section class="hero wrap">
  <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span>GST · Section 47</span>
  <h1>GST Late Fee <span class="grad-text">Calculator</span></h1>
  <p class="answer-first"><b>GST late fee under Section 47 is Rs.50 per day (Rs.25 CGST + Rs.25 SGST) for returns with tax, and Rs.20 per day (Rs.10 + Rs.10) for nil returns</b>, charged from the day after the due date until the return is filed, subject to a maximum cap based on annual turnover (Notification 07/2023-Central Tax).</p>
</section>

<div class="panel-wrap">
  <!-- ADSENSE SLOT — activate after approval -->
  <div class="calc-panel">
    <div class="field">
      <label>Return type</label>
      <select id="rtype">
        <option value="reg">GSTR-3B / GSTR-1 — with tax / turnover</option>
        <option value="nil">GSTR-3B / GSTR-1 — Nil return</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    <div class="row2">
      <div class="field"><label>Due date</label><input type="date" id="due"></div>
      <div class="field"><label>Actual filing date</label><input type="date" id="filed"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="field" id="turnoverWrap">
      <label>Annual aggregate turnover (for cap)</label>
      <select id="turnover">
        <option value="2000">Up to Rs.1.5 crore — cap Rs.2,000</option>
        <option value="5000">Rs.1.5 crore to Rs.5 crore — cap Rs.5,000</option>
        <option value="10000">Above Rs.5 crore — cap Rs.10,000</option>
      </select>
      <div class="hint">Caps per Notification 07/2023-Central Tax (combined CGST + SGST). Confirmed in force for FY 2026-27. ✓</div>
    </div>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" style="width:100%;margin-top:6px" onclick="calc()">Calculate late fee</button>
    <div id="out"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="prose" style="padding-top:30px">
    <h2>How the late fee is computed</h2>
    <p>The fee runs from the day <b>after</b> the due date to the date of filing (both-inclusive count of delayed days), at the per-day rate, and is then restricted to the maximum cap. CGST and SGST are charged equally; there is <b>no late fee under the IGST Act</b>.</p>
    <div class="callout law"><b>Section 47, CGST Act 2017</b> — late fee Rs.100/day per Act (Rs.200 combined) up to Rs.5,000; reduced for GSTR-3B/GSTR-1 to Rs.25/day per Act (Rs.50 combined; Rs.10 + Rs.10 for nil) by Notification 19/2021-CT, with turnover-based caps under Notification 07/2023-CT.</div>
    <div class="callout warn"><b>Note.</b> Late fee is separate from <a href="gst-interest-calculator.html">interest under Section 50</a>. This tool covers GSTR-1/3B; GSTR-9 late fee (Rs.200/day, turnover-based cap per Notif. 07/2023-CT) is separate — compute manually.</div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
      <details><summary>Is there late fee on the IGST portion?</summary><p>No. Late fee under Section 47 is levied only under the CGST Act and the respective SGST/UTGST Act — there is no late fee under the IGST Act.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Does a nil return attract late fee?</summary><p>Yes, a reduced fee of Rs.20 per day (Rs.10 CGST + Rs.10 SGST), capped at Rs.500 per return.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Is late fee waived if filed before the due date but tax paid late?</summary><p>No — late fee under Section 47 is for late <i>filing</i> of the return. Late <i>payment</i> of tax attracts interest under Section 50, which is a separate charge.</p></details>
    </div>

    <div class="key-takeaways"><h2>Key takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Rate: Rs.50/day (regular) or Rs.20/day (nil) — combined CGST + SGST.</li>
        <li>Counted from the day after the due date to the filing date.</li>
        <li>Capped by turnover under Notification 07/2023-CT.</li>
        <li>No IGST late fee; interest under Section 50 is separate.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
